# Line endings are load-bearing here.
#
# This repo is authored on Windows but its artifacts run on Linux. A shell
# script committed with CRLF has `#!/bin/sh\r` as its shebang, and the kernel
# looks for an interpreter literally named "sh\r" — the container then dies
# with the famously unhelpful:
#
#     exec /usr/local/bin/docker-entrypoint.sh: no such file or directory
#
# ...even though the file is plainly there. Caught 2026-07-22 when the image
# built from a fresh clone (the build-time smoke test runs the binary
# directly, so it passes; only the ENTRYPOINT path breaks).
#
# Force LF for everything a Linux system has to interpret.
*.sh text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
docker-entrypoint.sh text eol=lf

# JSON manifests are read by tooling on both platforms; keep them stable too.
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
